1897	\section{Out of scope}
1898	\label{sec:gr_out_of_scope}
1899	
1900	This chapter constructs the Grassmannian \emph{scheme} \(\mathrm{Gr}(r,d)\) over
1901	the absolute base \(\mathbb{Z}\) and establishes its smoothness, separatedness
1902	and properness. The following constructions are deferred to later chapters and
1903	are not treated here:
1904	\begin{itemize}
1905	  \item \textbf{The tautological/universal quotient} \(u : \mathcal{O}^{\oplus
1906	    r}_{\mathrm{Gr}(r,d)} \twoheadrightarrow \mathcal{U}\) and the determinant
1907	    line bundle \(\det \mathcal{U}\) with its Pl\"ucker embedding.
1908	  \item \textbf{The functor-of-points representability} of \(\mathrm{Gr}(r,d)\)
1909	    -- that it represents \(\mathrm{Grass}(r,d) =
1910	    \Quot^{d,\mathcal{O}_{\mathbb{Z}}}_{\oplus^r \mathcal{O}_{\mathbb{Z}} /
1911	    \mathbb{Z} / \mathbb{Z}}\); this is blueprinted as
1912	    \cref{thm:grassmannian_representable} in
1913	    \cref{chap:Picard_QuotScheme}.
1914	  \item \textbf{The relative version over a general base \(S\)} with a locally
1915	    free sheaf \(V\) of rank \(r\): the scheme \(\mathrm{Gr}_S(V,d)\) obtained by
1916	    base change and gluing over a trivialising cover of \(V\). The
1917	    absolute-over-\(\mathbb{Z}\) construction of this chapter is the input to
1918	    that base change.
1919	\end{itemize}
